folder: Roosevelt Avenue & Main Street (East)., Queens, NY
text:
Roosevelt Avenue, east from Main Street. View 2 shows the north side of the avenue at Main Street, viewing east across the latter. The office building, which houses the Bank of Manhattan, is at the N. E. corner of the two thoroughfares.
View 3 shows the buildings on the south side of the avenue, looking east from Main Street. The Flushing Institute formerly stood here.

View 1: Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

Views 2,3: P. L. Sperr

October 11, 1930
August 24, 1935
